    ('Martin Logan',39,'Programming','1933988789',500,100,'2010-11-16 00:00:00','Erlang and OTP in Action teaches you to apply Erlang''s shared-state model for concurrent programming--a completely different way of tackling the problem of parallel programming from the more common multi-threaded approach. This book walks you through the practical considerations and steps of building systems in Erlang and integrating them with real-world C/C++, Java, and .NET applications. Unlike other books on the market, Erlang and OTP in Action offers a comprehensive view of how concurrency relates to SOA and web technologies.','https://s3.amazonaws.com/AKIAJC5RLADLUMVRPFDQ.book-thumb-images/logan.jpg','Erlang and OTP in Action'),
